%global packname  samplingVarEst
%global packver   1.4
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          1.4
Release:          1%{?dist}
Summary:          Sampling Variance Estimation

License:          GPL (>= 2)
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel >= 3.1.0
Requires:         R-core >= 3.1.0

%description
Functions to calculate some point estimators and estimating their variance
under unequal probability sampling without replacement. Single and two
stage sampling designs are considered. Some approximations for the second
order inclusion probabilities (joint inclusion probabilities) are
available (sample and population based). A variety of Jackknife variance
estimators are implemented. Almost every function is written in C
(compiled) code for faster results. The functions incorporate some
performance improvements for faster results with large datasets.

